articles.description: Former Sen. Jim Demint (R-SC) announced on Thursday his endorsement of Judge Roy Moore in next week's Alabama U.S. senate race, in another blow to the establishment-backed candidate Luther Strange's campaign.

articles.author: Dan Riehl
articles.title: Surabian on Luther Strange: ‘How Can He Drain the Swamp When He Literally Is the Swamp?’
articles.description: Former White House political adviser Andy Surabian joined Breitbart News Daily SiriusXM host Raheem Kassam on Thursday to talk about the rally for Judge Roy Moore that former Alaska Gov. Sarah Palin and Dr. Sebastian Gorka, former deputy adviser to President Trump, will headline Thursday in Montgomery, Alabama, as well as the race in general.

articles.author: John Carney and Matthew Boyle
articles.title: Exclusive — Make Central America Great Again: Luther Strange Lobbied for Trade Deal That Drained Thousands of Alabama Jobs to Honduras, Mexico
articles.description: In a strange twist of fate, one of the key figures who helped bring about a transfer of jobs out of Alabama via a NAFTA-style free trade agreement with Central American countries is now campaigning for the Senate seat formerly occupied by Jeff Sessions. Even stranger still, his campaign ads promise that he will “Kill Unfair Trade Deals.” His name is Luther Strange.

articles.author: Virginia Hale
articles.title: Just Three Per Cent of over Two Million Migrant Arrivals Since 2015 Have Been Deported
articles.description: Only 75,000 of the 2.2 million people who sought asylum in Europe in 2015 and 2016 have been deported to their homelands after their claims were rejected, a report has found.

articles.author: Thomas D. Williams, Ph.D.
articles.title: Germany’s Populist AfD Party Poised for Important Gains in Sunday Elections
articles.description: As Germany gears up for next Sunday’s federal elections, there is a growing fear among the nation’s elite establishment that the conservative AfD party will do considerably better than polls indicate.

articles.author: AWR Hawkins
articles.title: Armed Texan Intervenes, Stops Alleged Sexual Assault of Female Jogger
articles.description: Court documents filed this week claim an armed good Samaritan intervened and stopped an alleged sexual assault after hearing a female runner scream.

articles.author: Chris Tomlinson
articles.title: Afghan Migrant Arrested for ‘Honour Killing’ His 14-Year-Old Sister
articles.description: An 18-year-old migrant from Afghanistan has been arrested in the Austrian capital of Vienna after police allege he stabbed his own 14-year-old sister to death in an apparent honour killing.

articles.author: Breitbart News
articles.title: Sour Grapes: Chris Christie Hurts Lt. Gov’s Campaign to Succeed Him
articles.description: Ryan Hutchins reports in Politico on the "contentious relationship" between New Jersey Governor Chris Christie and Lt. Governor Kim Guadagno who is seeking to succeed him.

articles.author: John Binder
articles.title: Chamber of Commerce ‘Urges’ Trump, Congress to ‘Quickly’ Pass Amnesty for Illegal Aliens
articles.description: The United States Chamber of Commerce is urging President Trump and Congress to "quickly" pass a widespread amnesty plan that would not only allow 800,000 illegal aliens to obtain a pathway to U.S. citizenship, but could also trigger a chain migration of at least four to six million foreign nationals flooding into the country.

articles.author: Pam Key
articles.title: Mika Brzezinski: ‘It’s Crazy’ Melania Does Not See Donald Trump Is a ‘Rude,’ ‘Mean,’ ‘Bully’
articles.description: Thursday on ABC’s “The View,” while discussing first lady Melania Trump’s speech to the U.N. General Assembly about combating cyber-bullying, MSNBC’s “Morning Joe” co-host Mika Brzezinski said “it’s crazy” the first lady would make such a speech without acknowledging her husband, President Donald Trump, was a “bully.” Brzezinski said, “Do you guys know she is married to the guy who tweeted I was bleeding badly from a facelift? Among other things, the guy is a bully. The guy is a bully up and down, whether it’s verbal, whether it’s written, whether it’s tweeted, he is rude, and he is mean to people. And I think it’s strange the first lady would make a speech on such a platform just completely not discussing the fact that her husband, the president of the United States, is a bully. It’s crazy.” Follow Pam Key on Twitter @pamkeyNEN

articles.author: Charlie Spiering
articles.title: Donald Trump: Puerto Rico ‘Absolutely Obliterated’ by Hurricane Maria
articles.description: President Donald Trump commented on the historic hurricane damage in Puerto Rico, promising to help rebuild the community.

articles.author: Warner Todd Huston
articles.title: USA Today Deeply Triggered by Border Wall that Supposedly Ruined a Golf Course
articles.description: USA Today Sports has found another reason to attack President Donald Trump's border wall with the story of a Texas golf course that was cut in half by a border fence erected to prevent people from crossing into the U.S. illegally.

articles.author: Warner Todd Huston
articles.title: Networks Could Lose $200 Million if NFL Ratings Slide Continues
articles.description: If NFL fans continue to turn away from football, the TV networks could lose as much as $200 million in earnings, according to a new report.

articles.author: John Nolte
articles.title: Nolte: Hollywood Reboots ‘The Terminator’ … for the Third Freakin’ Time
articles.description: From what I am able to glean from the various reports, the news is this: James Cameron, who exited the franchise after dropping the mic with 1991's Terminator 2: Judgment Day, is back. Not as director, as a producer who will oversee a writers room charged with dreaming up a brand new Terminator trilogy.

articles.title: Ann Coulter: They Don’t Call It ‘the Great Tweet of China’
articles.description: We were counting on Trump to fight for us on the border -- not with rallies, not with hats, not with tweets, but by building a wall. And yet, as of Wednesday this week, Trump will have been in office 243 days without having begun the wall.

articles.title: Poll: Mitch McConnell and Paul Ryan Hit New Lows with Republicans
articles.description: The latest NBC/Wall Street Journal poll shows that Republicans are increasingly dissatisfied with their leaders in Congress.

articles.title: Luther Strange Finance Chair Tied to Alabama Bribery Case
articles.description: Alabama Senator Luther Strange's campaign finance chair, Thompson Tractor CEO Mike Thompson, is listed on federal tax documents as an officer of the nonprofit Alliance for Jobs, which federal prosecutors say was used to bribe former Alabama state Representative Oliver Robinson, who pleaded guilty to federal corruption charges this month, AL.com's Kyle Whitmire and John Archibald report.

articles.author: Breitbart News
articles.title: Alabama State Rep: Luther Strange Not Telling Truth About Corruption Probe
articles.description: Alabama State Representative Ed Henry (R-Hartselle) is calling for the release of his grand jury testimony in connection with a corruption case involving former Alabama House Speaker Mike Hubbard. Henry says now-U.S. Senator Luther Strange, who is facing a runoff primary Senate election next week against conservative Judge Roy Moore, is not telling the truth behind the anti-corruption unit he led while serving as Alabama's attorney general.

articles.author: Breitbart News
articles.title: WaPo: Swamp Worries That a Luther Strange Defeat ‘Could Prompt Some GOP Senators to Retire’
articles.description: The Washington Post reports that, although President Donald Trump and his staff were hesitant to campaign in Alabama for establishment-friendly Luther Strange, Swamp Republicans forced the president's hand -- fearing that a victory for Judge Roy Moore would motivate several allies to retire from the Senate rather than face Breitbart-backed challengers in 2018.

articles.author: Breitbart News
articles.title: WaPo: Defiant Outsider Roy Moore Aims for ‘New Level of Disruption in the U.S. Senate’ Against the Swamp Status Quo
articles.description: The Washington Post profiles "outsider" candidate Judge Roy Moore, the frontrunner in Alabama's U.S. Senate primary runoff election, in an article published Thursday morning.

articles.title: Melania Trump: It Is Parents’ Responsibility to Raise Children Who Have Moral Clarity, Love of Country
articles.description: Melania Trump said on Wednesday that peace, human rights, and human dignity — especially for vulnerable children — will be the pillars of the work she does in her role as first lady of the United States.

articles.description: Pope Francis met with the secretary general of the Muslim World League (MWL) in the Vatican Wednesday, a group that has been tied to Saudi financing of jihadist terrorism and the 9/11 attacks in 2001.

articles.title: Swedish Journalist Shot in No-Go Zone

articles.title: Exclusive: London Hospital Canteen Only Serves Halal Meat

articles.description: City attorneys in San Francisco and Oakland, California, sued five oil companies in two coordinated lawsuits on Tuesday, arguing that the courts should hold these companies responsible for climate change, and force them to financially compensate the cities for harm the plaintiffs claim those companies are causing to the planet’s environment.

articles.title: ‘He Will Let You Know’ — Rex Tillerson Confirms Donald Trump Decision on Iran Deal

articles.title: Pollak: The ‘Resistance’ Is on the Ballot in Alabama, Not California
articles.description: Ironically, the most effective force "resisting" President Donald Trump's agenda is not the Democratic Party or the institutional left, but the Republican-held Congress and the Beltway political establishment to which it is anchored.

articles.title: Swamp Co-Opts Trump to Campaign for Luther Strange to Protect GOP Establishment from Breitbart-Backed Grassroots Challengers
